      <hedline>
        <hl1>Politics of Abortion: The Debate Rages</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Gabrielle B Britton letter on Oct 11 editorial on women's right to choose abortion; says it is disheartening that Gov George W Bush and Republican Party do not trust people (and women in particular) when it comes to their bodies</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Enduring Battle Over Choice'' (editorial, Oct. 11):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Enduring Battle Over Choice'' (editorial, Oct. 11):</p>
        <p>It is disheartening that Gov. George W. Bush continues to emphasize that the American people should be trusted with the surplus, while the Republican platform simultaneously calls for a constitutional ban on abortion.</p>
        <p>Isn't it ironic that Republicans trust the American people with the surplus but do not trust the people (and women in particular) when it comes to their bodies?</p>
        <p>GABRIELLE B. BRITTON  Bloomington, Ind., Oct. 11, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
